Defendant Bryson T Tompkins in court, in custody, with attorney John Paul Marchan.   Shawn N Woller appeared for the State of Wisconsin.    The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

IMPOSED SENTENCE of: 

5 YEARS 3 MONTHS IMPRISONMENT
  -  2 YEAR(S)  3 MONTHS OF INITIAL CONFINEMENT (CONSECUTIVE TO 15CF239);
  -  3 YEAR(S) OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION;

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
*No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia.
*No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
*Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed.
*Inform Agent of all prescriptions
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
*Maintain full time employment and/or combination of schooling 
or any other deemed appropriate by agent;
*DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done.
*100 Hours of Community Service.
*Obtain GED or HSED;

RESTITUTION:  $189.98 payable to  Chelsea C. (to be paid as a condition of extended supervision - restitution to be paid before costs or fines);

COURT COSTS:  $268.00 (to be paid as a condition of extended supervision);

DNA SURCHARGE:  $250.00 (to be paid as a condition of extended supervision);

Defendant is eligible for Challenge Incarceration Program.(after two years initial confinement)
Defendant is eligible for Substance Abuse Program. (after two years initial confinement)

Felony warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.
